Ok this is how I got this working and activated... I installed Windows 8 Pro with Media Center x86 (I'm sure you can do the x64 version the same). After installing I noticed it wasn't activated. (I didn't use any of the activators that came with the torrent) So I went to this site. 
http://windows.microsoft.com/en-US/windows-8/feature-packs

Windows is giving away serial keys for free for the Media Center add-on. No joke. Just type in an email and they send you one.

So for shits and giggles I tried it and got a serial and added it through this process.

Once you obtain your key, go to the search tool (looks like a magnifying glass on the right side of the screen) and under "Apps" type in SLUI 3

This will pull up an activation window where you can paste or type in your key. Now my copy is activated. I don't know if this is some sort of loophole but it worked for me. 

Note that you can only use one serial per computer and Microsoft is giving these keys away for a limited time. 

Let me know if this works for any of you as well.

Also, THANKS FOR THE TORRENT :)

If anyone installed (Anti-Virus) and you are seeing a black screen after you log-in. Here is what you need to do to fix that problem:
0: Go to Processes and select one (any) and right click and select Open file location to open explorer and go to control panel and uninstall your anti-virus.
1: Press Ctrl + Alt + Delete 
2: Run Task Manager
3: Select File from top menu and open (Run New Task)
4: Click Browse and Find the crack (Activator) and select and (Right-Click) and Run as Administrator. Y = yes.

After updates are installed you're OS will be deactivated so Run the Activator if so.
